Hi! I'm Pushpita Mondal! I hope you are all safe and healthy.

I'm introducing my youtube channel with my first dance (Shadow mudra) video. The video is about her arrival, yes 80 days are left for arrival of Maa Durga, and during this period of crisis we are all hoping for some glimmer of positivity. .
More videos to come. Please do support me by liking, sharing and subscribing to my channel.

French Fries ?
Do these need any introduction? 
Missing munching on French fries, don't you worry!
Try French Fries at home with these simple easy steps with yummy white sauce as well! 
.
Recipe:
Ingredients needed:

•For White Sauce:
1. 1/2 tbsp Butter
2. 1 tsp finely chopped Garlic
3. 1/2 tbsp All purpose flour/maida
4. 1/4th cup Milk 
5. 1 Cheese Slice
6. Pinch of Salt

Process:
Take a sauce pan add Butter, then add garlic saute it for 10-15 secs then add 1/2 tbsp All purpose flour/maida then stir it very well at low to medium flame, then add milk keep stirring continuously to avoid lumps, you can even add little water to get more consistency if required, then add cheese slice, you can even add more cheese  and stir it very well, add pinch of salt.

• French Fries?: 
Process:
1. Take 2-3 Big sized potatoes, wash and peel them then cut it into shape of fries.
2. Rinse and soak in ice cold water for 15 mins.
3. After that remove them and pat dry using a dry kitchen towel to remove excess of water.
4. First Fry: Fry them on medium flame  for 2-3 mins.
5. Remove them, drain excess of oil and let it rest for 15 mins.
6. Second Fry: Fry them on high flame until crisp and golden brown in colour.
7. Season the fries with Salt and Black pepper powder as soon you remove from oil. 
8. Serve this Crispy French Fries with Cheesy white sauce.
 Enjoyy!

Why do I not post Mandalas regularly?

I hate the fact that I’m not regular with my posting schedule. But, you have to understand that making a Mandala requires some time and patience. You have to sit down in one place for atleast a couple of hours. And during my regular college days, that’s like asking way too much from myself. For me, drawing Mandalas was always about taking a break from the monotony of life. So, I make Mandalas when I feel like making them. When I know that making them would bring me the much required inner peace and strength! 

Here’s a little mini-Mandalas beauty that I created! Once again, I would like to say that my work isn’t the finest right now, but I’m taking baby steps. ??

P.S - You’ll always find Pencil markings! ? I’m just too scared to erase them lest it disturbs the art. ?
